    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that starts in the lining of the inside of your cheek (the soft tissue covering the inside wall of your mouth). This type of cancer typically develops when cells in the cheek's mucous membrane grow abnormally and become malignant, often due to factors like tobacco use, alcohol consumption, or other irritants. You might notice a persistent sore, lump, or discolored patch inside your cheek that doesn't heal.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, head and neck surgeons, and otolaryngologists (ENT specialists) use this code when diagnosing and treating oral cancers. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, biopsies, imaging studies, or surgical procedures related to cheek mucosal cancer.",
