    "rawCode": "C223",
    "shortDesc": "Angiosarcoma of liver",
    "longDesc": "Angiosarcoma of liver",
    "plainEnglish": "Angiosarcoma of the liver is a rare, aggressive cancer that starts in the blood vessels of the liver. This tumor grows quickly and is caused by abnormal cells in the vessel lining multiplying uncontrollably. Patients may experience abdominal pain, swelling in the belly, jaundice (yellowing of skin and eyes), fatigue, and weight loss, though early stages often have no symptoms.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, hepatologists, and surgical oncologists use this code when diagnosing and treating liver cancer patients. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing chemotherapy, imaging studies, or liver surgery, as angiosarcoma requires aggressive treatment planning and coordination of care.",
