    "shortDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of short bones of right upper limb",
    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of short bones of right upper limb",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has started in the small bones of the right arm or hand, such as the bones in the wrist, fingers, or forearm. These are called \"short bones\" because they're smaller than the long arm bones (like the humerus), and cancer in these locations is relatively rare. Patients may notice a lump, swelling, pain, or weakness in the affected area of the right arm.",
