    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of long bones of right lower limb",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that starts in the long bones of the right leg, such as the thighbone (femur), shinbone (tibia), or fibula. These are aggressive cancers that grow in the main shaft or length of the bone and can spread to other parts of the body if not treated. Patients may experience pain, swelling, or a noticeable lump in the affected leg.",
