    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of long bones of left lower limb",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a malignant (cancerous) tumor that develops in one of the long bones of the left leg, such as the thighbone (femur), shinbone (tibia), or fibula. These tumors typically arise from bone cells themselves and can cause pain, swelling, or weakening of the affected leg. Without treatment, bone cancers can spread to other parts of the body, making early detection and treatment important.",
    "whoUses": "Orthopedic oncologists, medical oncologists, and orthopedic surgeons use this code when diagnosing and treating primary bone cancers in the left leg. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, surgical consultation, or limb-salvaging procedures, and is essential for tracking cancer treatment and follow-up care.",
