    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that starts in the bones of the spine (vertebrae). The vertebral column is made up of individual bones stacked on top of each other that protect the spinal cord and support your back. When cancer develops in these bones, it can cause pain, weakness, or numbness in the back or limbs, and may affect movement or nerve function.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, orthopedic surgeons, and spine specialists use this code when diagnosing and treating primary bone cancers of the spine. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, imaging studies, or spine surgery consultations, and indicates a serious malignancy requiring specialized cancer care.",
