    "shortDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of ribs, sternum and clavicle",
    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of ribs, sternum and clavicle",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has started in the bones of the chest wall, specifically in the ribs (the curved bones around your lungs), sternum (the flat bone in the center of your chest), or clavicle (your collarbone). These are solid bone cancers rather than cancers that have spread from elsewhere, and they're aggressive tumors that require aggressive treatment. You might notice pain in the chest wall, a lump or swelling, or discomfort when moving or breathing.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, orthopedic surgeons, and thoracic surgeons use this code when diagnosing and treating primary bone cancers of the chest wall. This code commonly appears in hospital discharge summaries and specialist referrals, and may appear on EOB statements for patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, or surgical removal of the affected bone.",
