    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a type of skin cancer called melanoma that has developed on the trunk of the body—which includes the chest, back, abdomen, and sides—in areas not specifically classified elsewhere. Melanoma is the most dangerous type of skin cancer because it arises from pigment-producing cells and can spread to other parts of the body if not treated early. It typically appears as a dark, irregularly shaped mole or spot that may be growing, bleeding, or changing in appearance.",
    "whoUses": "Dermatologists, surgical oncologists, and medical oncologists use this code when diagnosing and treating melanoma of the trunk. It commonly appears on EOB statements and medical records for patients undergoing skin biopsies, surgical excisions, chemotherapy, or immunotherapy for trunk melanomas.",
