    "longDesc": "Merkel cell carcinoma of right lower limb, including hip",
    "plainEnglish": "Merkel cell carcinoma is a rare, aggressive skin cancer that develops from special nerve-sensing cells in the skin called Merkel cells. In this case, the cancer is located on the right lower leg or hip area and tends to grow quickly and spread to other parts of the body if not treated early. It typically appears as a firm, painless nodule or bump on the skin, often red or purple in color.",
    "whoUses": "Dermatologists, oncologists, and surgical specialists use this code when diagnosing and treating Merkel cell carcinoma. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements and medical records for patients undergoing skin biopsies, cancer staging, surgical removal, or chemotherapy related to this malignancy.",
