    "plainEnglish": "Basal cell carcinoma is a type of skin cancer that starts in the basal cells, the deepest layer of skin, and in this case occurs on the lip. It typically appears as a small, waxy, or pearly bump that may bleed, crust over, or not heal properly. While it's the most common type of skin cancer, it grows slowly and rarely spreads to other parts of the body, making it highly treatable when caught early.",
