    "rawCode": "C44311",
    "shortDesc": "Basal cell carcinoma of skin of nose",
    "longDesc": "Basal cell carcinoma of skin of nose",
    "plainEnglish": "Basal cell carcinoma is the most common type of skin cancer, occurring in the outermost layer of skin cells on the nose. It typically develops from years of sun exposure and appears as a small, shiny bump, scaly patch, or sore that doesn't heal properly on the nose. While it grows slowly and rarely spreads to other parts of the body, it does need to be removed to prevent it from damaging the nose tissue and affecting your appearance.",
    "whoUses": "Dermatologists and general practitioners diagnose and treat this condition, often with surgical removal, laser therapy, or topical medications. This code frequently appears on patient EOBs when biopsies, excisions, or other skin cancer treatments are performed on the nasal area.",
