    "shortDesc": "Squamous cell carcinoma of anal skin",
    "longDesc": "Squamous cell carcinoma of anal skin",
    "plainEnglish": "This is a type of skin cancer that develops on the outer skin surface around the anus, caused by abnormal growth of squamous cells (the flat cells that make up the outer layer of skin). It typically appears as a bump, sore, or discolored area that may bleed, itch, or be painful, and is often associated with sun exposure, HPV infection, or chronic irritation.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by dermatologists, oncologists, colorectal surgeons, and general practitioners when diagnosing and treating anal skin cancer. It commonly appears on EOB statements as a cancer diagnosis that requires pathological confirmation and typically leads to treatment referrals and ongoing oncology care.",
