    "longDesc": "Squamous cell carcinoma of skin of breast",
    "plainEnglish": "Squamous cell carcinoma of the breast is a type of skin cancer that develops on the outer layer of skin covering the breast. This cancer originates from flat, scale-like cells called squamous cells and typically appears as a slowly growing, scaly patch, bump, or sore that may bleed or not heal properly. It's usually caused by prolonged sun exposure, though breast skin cancer can also develop in areas that aren't commonly exposed to the sun.",
    "whoUses": "Dermatologists, oncologists, and surgical oncologists use this code when diagnosing and treating skin cancers of the breast. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing biopsies, Mohs surgery, or wider surgical excision of the affected skin area, along with associated pathology and imaging services.",
