    "plainEnglish": "This code refers to a cancer of the skin that is not one of the three most common types (melanoma, basal cell carcinoma, or squamous cell carcinoma). It represents a rare or unusual type of skin cancer that the doctor has specifically identified but doesn't fit into the standard categories. These cancers typically develop from abnormal skin cells that multiply uncontrollably and can spread to other parts of the body if not treated.",
    "whoUses": "Dermatologists, oncologists, and surgical specialists use this code when diagnosing and treating uncommon skin cancers such as Merkel cell carcinoma, sebaceous gland carcinoma, or other rare skin malignancies. This code frequently appears on EOB statements as it indicates a malignant condition requiring active treatment and close follow-up care.",
