    "longDesc": "Mesothelioma of pleura",
    "plainEnglish": "Mesothelioma of the pleura is a rare but aggressive cancer that develops in the thin lining surrounding the lungs (called the pleura). It's almost always caused by inhaling asbestos fibers, often years or even decades before symptoms appear. People with this condition may experience chest pain, persistent cough, shortness of breath, and fluid buildup around the lungs.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, pulmonologists, and thoracic surgeons diagnose and treat this condition, often using imaging and biopsies to confirm it. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, surgery, or palliative care, as mesothelioma typically requires intensive treatment and specialist care.",
