    "shortDesc": "Mesothelioma of peritoneum",
    "longDesc": "Mesothelioma of peritoneum",
    "plainEnglish": "Mesothelioma of the peritoneum is a serious cancer that develops in the thin lining (peritoneum) that covers the organs inside your abdomen. It's caused by inhaling or ingesting asbestos fibers, which can remain in the body for decades before causing cancer. People with this condition may experience abdominal swelling, pain, fluid buildup in the belly, and gastrointestinal symptoms.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, gastroenterologists, and thoracic surgeons diagnose and treat peritoneal mesothelioma, often working with pathologists who confirm the diagnosis through biopsies. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with confirmed mesothelioma seeking chemotherapy, surgery, or palliative care, and is frequently associated with workers' compensation claims due to occupational asbestos exposure.",
