    "shortDesc": "Mesothelioma of pericardium",
    "longDesc": "Mesothelioma of pericardium",
    "plainEnglish": "Mesothelioma of the pericardium is a rare and aggressive cancer that develops in the thin membrane (called the pericardium) surrounding the heart. This cancer is caused by exposure to asbestos fibers that were inhaled or ingested years or even decades earlier, and the fibers settled in the heart lining where they triggered cancerous cell growth. Symptoms may include chest pain, shortness of breath, heart palpitations, and fluid accumulation around the heart, though the disease is often diagnosed only in advanced stages.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, cardiologists, and thoracic surgeons typically use this code when diagnosing and treating pericardial mesothelioma patients. This is a serious diagnosis that commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with documented asbestos exposure histories who receive chemotherapy, radiation, or surgical interventions for their condition.",
