    "shortDesc": "Mesothelioma of other sites",
    "longDesc": "Mesothelioma of other sites",
    "plainEnglish": "Mesothelioma is a rare and aggressive cancer that develops in the thin layer of tissue covering most internal organs, caused almost exclusively by exposure to asbestos fibers. When mesothelioma occurs in locations other than the lungs, heart lining, or abdominal lining (such as the testicles or other rare sites), it is classified as mesothelioma of other sites. The disease typically develops 20-50 years after asbestos exposure and causes symptoms like pain, swelling, or fluid buildup in the affected area.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, pulmonologists, and surgical specialists use this code when diagnosing and treating mesothelioma in unusual anatomical locations. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements for those with documented asbestos exposure and cancer diagnoses, often in workers' compensation claims or mesothelioma litigation cases.",
