    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of peripheral nerves of thorax",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a cancer that starts in the peripheral nerves (the nerves outside the brain and spinal cord) located in the chest area. These nerves normally carry signals between your chest organs and your brain, but in this case, cancer cells have developed in the nerve tissue itself. This is a serious condition that typically causes pain, weakness, or numbness in the affected area of the chest.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists (cancer specialists) and surgical oncologists use this code when diagnosing and treating nerve cancers in the chest region, often in collaboration with thoracic surgeons. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, or surgical treatment for peripheral nerve tumors in the thorax.",
