    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of retroperitoneum",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that starts in the retroperitoneum, which is the area behind the abdominal lining where important organs and blood vessels are located. These tumors can grow from fat, connective tissue, or blood vessels in this deep abdominal space and may not cause symptoms until they become quite large. People might experience back pain, abdominal swelling, or feel a mass in their belly, but symptoms often appear late because the tumor has room to grow before pressing on nearby structures.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, surgical oncologists, and abdominal surgeons use this code when diagnosing and treating retroperitoneal cancers, which are rare tumors requiring specialized imaging and often complex surgery. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, as it guides staging, treatment planning, and insurance coverage for chemotherapy, surgery, or radiation therapy.",
