    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has started in a specific area of the peritoneum, which is the thin membrane lining the inside of your abdomen and covering most of your organs. This is a serious condition where cancer cells have begun growing in this tissue lining, and it typically causes abdominal pain, swelling, or changes in bowel habits. Unlike peritoneal cancer that spreads from other organs, this type originates directly in the peritoneum itself.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, surgical oncologists, and gastroenterologists commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating primary peritoneal cancer. It frequently appears on EOB statements for cancer patients undergoing chemotherapy, surgery, or imaging studies related to abdominal malignancy.",
