    "rawCode": "C493",
    "shortDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of connective and soft tissue of thorax",
    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of connective and soft tissue of thorax",
    "plainEnglish": "This code represents cancer that starts in the soft tissues of the chest, such as muscles, fat, or fibrous tissue surrounding the lungs and heart. These cancers, called sarcomas, grow from the supportive tissues rather than from organs themselves, and can spread to other parts of the body if not treated. Patients may notice a lump in the chest, chest pain, or difficulty breathing depending on where the tumor is located.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, thoracic surgeons, and pathologists use this code when diagnosing and treating soft tissue sarcomas in the chest cavity. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, or surgical removal of chest wall tumors, and is used for tracking cancer treatment and monitoring.",
