    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of connective and soft tissue of pelvis",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that develops in the connective and soft tissues of the pelvis—the area between your hip bones that holds organs like the bladder and reproductive organs. These are usually aggressive tumors that arise from fat, muscle, or fibrous tissue rather than from the organs themselves. Patients may notice a growing mass or lump in the pelvic area, along with pain, pressure, or difficulty with bowel or bladder function.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, sarcoma specialists, and surgical oncologists commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating soft tissue cancers in the pelvis. This code frequently appears on EOB statements as it requires extensive workup, imaging, and often surgical intervention or chemotherapy, making it a significant diagnostic and treatment descriptor in cancer care.",
