    "rawCode": "C49A0",
    "shortDesc": "Gastrointestinal stromal tumor, unspecified site",
    "longDesc": "Gastrointestinal stromal tumor, unspecified site",
    "plainEnglish": "A gastrointestinal stromal tumor (GIST) is a rare type of cancer that starts in the cells lining your digestive tract (stomach, small intestine, or colon). These tumors grow from special nerve cells in the digestive system and can range from slow-growing to aggressive. Symptoms may include abdominal pain, bleeding, or a feeling of fullness, though some people have no symptoms until the tumor is found.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, gastroenterologists, and general surgeons most commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating GISTs. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing imaging, biopsies, chemotherapy, or surgical removal of the tumor, as GISTs require specialized cancer care and monitoring.",
