    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of axillary tail of right female breast",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes breast cancer that has started in the axillary tail, which is the upper outer portion of the right breast that extends toward the armpit. This area is sometimes called the \"tail of Spence\" and accounts for a significant portion of breast cancers. The patient would typically notice a lump, thickening, or other abnormality in this specific region of the breast.",
