    "plainEnglish": "This code describes breast cancer that has developed specifically in the axillary tail of the left breast—that's the section of breast tissue that extends toward the armpit. The axillary tail is a normal part of breast anatomy and, like any breast tissue, can develop cancer cells. A woman with this diagnosis would have been found to have a malignant (cancerous) tumor in this specific location of her left breast.",
