    "rawCode": "C6951",
    "shortDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of right lacrimal gland and duct",
    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of right lacrimal gland and duct",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has started in the lacrimal gland (tear gland) or its duct on the right side of your eye. The lacrimal gland produces tears to keep your eye moist, and when cancer develops there, it's a serious condition that requires treatment. You might notice symptoms like a lump near the upper outer corner of your right eye, eye pain, or vision changes.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, ophthalmologists, and otolaryngologists (ENT specialists) use this code when diagnosing and treating lacrimal gland cancers. It commonly appears on EOB statements for cancer patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, or surgical removal of the affected gland, and is tracked by cancer registries for treatment outcomes.",
