    "rawCode": "C6960",
    "shortDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of unspecified orbit",
    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of unspecified orbit",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has started in the orbit, which is the bony socket that holds your eyeball and the muscles that move it. The cancer originates in the tissue of the eye socket itself rather than in the eyeball, and in this case, doctors haven't identified the specific type of tissue where the cancer began. This is a serious condition that typically causes symptoms like eye bulging, vision changes, or pain around the eye.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, ophthalmologists, and orbital surgeons use this code when diagnosing and treating orbital cancers. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, imaging studies, or biopsies related to orbital masses, and is typically used in hospital or specialty cancer center settings.",
