    "longDesc": "Malignant neoplasm of right orbit",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has developed in the tissues and structures of the right eye socket (orbit), which is the bony cavity that holds and protects the eyeball and its supporting muscles and nerves. This is a serious condition where cancer cells are actively growing in this area, and it can affect vision, eye movement, and the structures around the eye. The cancer may originate in the orbit itself or have spread there from another part of the body.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, ophthalmologists, and otolaryngologists (ENT specialists) use this code when diagnosing and treating orbital cancers. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, imaging studies, or consultations related to malignant orbital tumors, and is essential for cancer registry reporting and treatment planning.",
