    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has developed in the left eye socket (orbit), which is the bony cavity that holds the eyeball and its supporting structures. Unlike eye cancers that start in the eyeball itself, this cancer originates in the tissues around and behind the eye, such as muscles, nerves, or fat. Symptoms may include a bulging eye, vision problems, eye pain, or a visible mass.",
