    "plainEnglish": "This is cancer that starts in the meninges, the thin layers of tissue that wrap around and protect the brain. This type of cancer causes abnormal cells to grow in these protective membranes, which can put pressure on the brain and interfere with its normal function, potentially causing headaches, vision problems, weakness, or cognitive changes.",
