    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer of the parathyroid glands, four tiny glands in your neck that control calcium levels in your blood. When cancer develops in these glands, abnormal cells grow and multiply uncontrollably, potentially spreading to other parts of the body. People with parathyroid cancer may experience high blood calcium levels (causing weakness, nausea, or kidney problems), neck lumps, or voice changes.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, endocrinologists, and head and neck surgeons use this code when diagnosing and treating parathyroid cancer. It appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, surgery, or oncology consultations, though parathyroid cancer is relatively rare compared to other malignancies.",
