    "plainEnglish": "A carcinoid tumor is a rare type of cancer that grows very slowly and starts in cells that produce hormones. When the location of the tumor is unknown or not specified, this code is used to classify it. These tumors can occur in various parts of the body, often in the digestive system or lungs, and may cause symptoms like flushing, diarrhea, or heart problems if the cancer spreads or releases large amounts of hormones into the bloodstream.",
