    "plainEnglish": "A malignant carcinoid tumor of the duodenum is a type of cancer that starts in the duodenum, which is the first part of your small intestine. Carcinoid tumors grow from special hormone-producing cells in the intestine and tend to grow slowly compared to other cancers, but they are still dangerous and can spread to other parts of the body. Symptoms may include abdominal pain, diarrhea, or flushing of the skin, though some people have no symptoms until the cancer is found during testing for other reasons.",
