    "plainEnglish": "A malignant carcinoid tumor is a rare type of cancer that starts in neuroendocrine cells (special hormone-producing cells) in the hindgut, which includes the lower part of your colon and rectum. These tumors grow slowly and can produce excess hormones that cause symptoms like diarrhea, flushing, and abdominal cramping. The 'unspecified' part means the exact location within the hindgut hasn't been identified as precisely as possible, so more testing may be needed to determine exactly where the tumor is.",
