    "code": "C78.00",
    "rawCode": "C7800",
    "shortDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of unspecified lung",
    "longDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of unspecified lung",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has spread to the lungs from another part of the body (rather than cancer that started in the lungs). When cancer cells from a tumor elsewhere travel through the bloodstream or lymphatic system and establish themselves in the lung tissue, it's called secondary lung cancer or metastatic lung cancer. Patients may experience symptoms like coughing, chest pain, shortness of breath, or no symptoms at all, depending on the size and location of the tumors.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, pulmonologists, and hospitalists use this code when documenting metastatic cancer to the lungs in patients with a known primary cancer elsewhere. It commonly appears on EOB statements and medical records for patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, or other cancer treatments, as it's essential for staging and treatment planning.",
    "billable": true,
    "isNew": false,
    "isRevised": false,
