    "shortDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of right lung",
    "longDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of right lung",
    "plainEnglish": "This code means cancer has spread to the right lung from another part of the body (rather than starting in the lung itself). The original cancer could have come from the breast, colon, kidney, or other organs, and cancer cells traveled through the bloodstream or lymph system to settle in the right lung. Patients may experience coughing, chest pain, shortness of breath, or no symptoms at all, depending on how much cancer has spread.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, pulmonologists, and thoracic surgeons use this code when diagnosing and treating metastatic lung cancer. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements when imaging (CT scans) or biopsies confirm cancer spread to the lung, and is essential for tracking treatment and insurance coverage for chemotherapy or radiation therapy targeting the lungs.",
