    "shortDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of left lung",
    "longDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of left lung",
    "plainEnglish": "This code means that cancer has spread to the left lung from another part of the body where it originally started. Secondary cancer is not new cancer that began in the lung itself, but rather cancer cells that traveled through the bloodstream or lymphatic system from a primary cancer elsewhere (such as the breast, colon, or kidney). Patients may experience symptoms like cough, shortness of breath, chest pain, or may have no symptoms at all until the spread is discovered on imaging.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, pulmonologists, and thoracic surgeons use this code when documenting metastatic disease involving the left lung. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, imaging studies (CT scans), biopsies, or consultations related to their metastatic disease.",
