    "shortDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of mediastinum",
    "longDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of mediastinum",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that cancer has spread to the mediastinum, which is the central compartment of your chest between your lungs that contains the heart, esophagus, and major blood vessels. This is not a new cancer starting in the mediastinum, but rather cancer that originated elsewhere in the body and has traveled there. This spreading typically causes symptoms like chest pain, difficulty swallowing, cough, or shortness of breath.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, pulmonologists, thoracic surgeons, and pathologists use this code when diagnosing and staging metastatic cancer, typically discovered through imaging (CT, PET scans) or biopsy. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients with advanced cancer receiving chemotherapy, radiation, or surgical consultation for metastatic disease management.",
