    "plainEnglish": "This code describes cancer that has spread to the pleura, which is the thin membrane surrounding the lungs. Rather than starting in the pleura itself, this cancer originated elsewhere in the body (such as the lungs, breast, or stomach) and metastasized to this location. Patients may experience chest pain, persistent cough, shortness of breath, or fluid buildup around the lungs.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, pulmonologists, and thoracic surgeons use this code when treating patients with advanced cancer that has spread to the pleural lining. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation, pleural fluid drainage procedures, or palliative care related to metastatic disease.",
