    "shortDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of bone",
    "longDesc": "Secondary malignant neoplasm of bone",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that cancer has spread from another part of the body to the bone. Rather than the cancer starting in the bone itself, it originated elsewhere (such as the breast, lung, or prostate) and metastasized, meaning cancer cells traveled through the bloodstream or lymphatic system and settled in bone tissue. Patients may experience bone pain, weakness, fractures, or numbness depending on which bones are affected.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, orthopedic surgeons, and palliative care specialists use this code when managing patients with metastatic cancer. It commonly appears in hospital inpatient records, oncology clinic notes, and patient EOB statements, as it indicates advanced cancer that requires ongoing systemic treatment and may involve imaging studies, bone-targeted medications, or radiation therapy.",
