    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that cancer has spread to one or both ovaries from another part of the body where it originally started. The cancer cells that develop in the ovaries are not new cancers but rather cancer that metastasized (traveled) from a primary tumor elsewhere, such as the colon, stomach, breast, or other organs. Patients may experience abdominal pain, bloating, abnormal vaginal bleeding, or no symptoms at all, depending on the size and location of the metastatic tumors.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, gynecologic oncologists, and pathologists use this code when diagnosing and treating metastatic ovarian cancer. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, imaging studies, or consultations related to secondary ovarian malignancies, and is essential for tracking stage and treatment planning in cancer care.",
