    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a specific type of blood cancer called Hodgkin lymphoma that has spread to or is primarily located in the spleen. Nodular sclerosis is the most common subtype of Hodgkin lymphoma, characterized by abnormal lymph cells that form clumps or nodules in lymph tissue. Patients may experience swelling of the spleen, fatigue, fever, night sweats, and swollen lymph nodes.",
