    "rawCode": "C8146",
    "shortDesc": "Lymphocyte-rich Hodgkin lymphoma, intrapelvic lymph nodes",
    "longDesc": "Lymphocyte-rich Hodgkin lymphoma, intrapelvic lymph nodes",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a specific type of cancer called Hodgkin lymphoma that is primarily composed of lymphocytes (a type of white blood cell) and has spread to or originated in the lymph nodes located inside the pelvis (the area between your hip bones). Hodgkin lymphoma is a cancer of the lymphatic system that causes these lymph nodes to grow abnormally and can affect overall immune function. Patients may notice swollen lymph nodes in the lower abdomen or pelvis, along with symptoms like fatigue, fever, or unexplained weight loss.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists and hematologists use this code when diagnosing and treating patients with Hodgkin lymphoma, particularly when imaging studies confirm involvement of pelvic lymph nodes. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for cancer patients undergoing chemotherapy, radiation therapy, or other cancer treatments, and is essential for tracking treatment responses and staging.",
